We - we had a go cart. And of course I had very little - I had very little leisure time to meself as a - you know 
- 'cos you see the average kid'd be able to go out and - enjoy himself with his pals but I - I - I had very little of that because - you see, I was always in charge of the younger ones. See? Oh I - I used to have one pal, you know, and - occasionally I'd 
be - allowed to go out with him - he - he was a schoolboy pal you know. 'Course we were friend right up 'til - well, I daresay the poor chaps dead now, but we were quite good friends after we grew up, you know, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9141532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid656999\charrsid7276462 Where would you go when you went out with him?
