 in and the deeds of it you know. But it didn't happen. But I had a money box and - I was taught as a - a small boy I was taught not to accept anything from anybody, see. I - I used to - no thank you. Father's got some, see. But I - of course I had to hav
e a money box but I was never allowed to spend any and - never had any pocket money. Nobody - we didn't have pocket money in those days.
