Well they - you see, to be a policeman in those days you wanted to be a big fellow with a big first. You didn't have to know anything. I mean a policeman is an educated man today. He is. He must k
now quite a bit. - But in those days it didn't matter. Well - they'd just mooch about. They used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Great Peter Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - was such a rough place - they'd go down there four at a time. Yes. Yes, four at a time. One - if there was one went down there - he'd get a good hiding.
