hour a day and - an hour on Saturdays and Sundays. Well I used to keep 'em up to that as far as possible, see, and now and again they'd slip, see. Here you owe me half an hour, see, but - when they grew up they wouldn't do anything about it. I used to say
 
to her when they were grown up - what about giving us a tune. Sorry dad, we - we've got to go out - got a netball match or something. See? So in the finish I said, well I don't know. It seems to me the only used this piano is is for me to knock meself on 
