at used to happen. Suppose - we'll assume that it's a large household - a real aristocrat household and - they have visit-ors. And the visitors bring their own servant or coachman or whatever and - in the servants hall they used to have a long table you k
n
ow and they sit there and according to their rank. Housekeeper - the housekeeper one end and the butler at the other, see, and these other people sat according to their rank in the house but - if a - if two people came, we'll - say - one was a Lord and - 
one was only a Sir - a knight you know, well the - their servants used to take the same precedence as their masters. Oh they - oh yes, they used to -
