 and - and, you know - I have worked up 'til - now on one occasion I can recall, going on duty early Christmas - Christmas Eve and - I
 was scheduled to finish round about nine o'clock. And it - we was cluttered up with work, oh, you'll have to stop to midnight. Right. Then midnight - had to stop all night and - and then - and - really without a break up 'til six o'clock next night. Well
 what - what used is a chap then? You see? Of course that's what they call the exist - exigencies of the service.
