\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9141532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid656999\charrsid7276462 Do you ever remember your wife making any medicines at all for the family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6448152 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid656999\charrsid7276462 
Oh well - such as cough mixture and - do you know, when I was a boy, mother used to make coug
h mixture. I - I'd be sent out, I'd have to go to the oil shop - and get some they had sort of tanks with taps, and - treacle. And I'd have to get - a couple of penn'orth of treacle or a pennyworth of treacle and then - and - then I'd get - take it see, i
n a basin, and then I'd go to the chemist and get some - what the devil is that stuff called, I forget now - oh and there was - and you - you had to have vinegar in it.
